"Linear Feedback Shift Registers (LFSRs) and Feedback with Carry Shift Registers (FCSRs) are two pseudo-random generators which are widely used in many cryptographic applications. The Ring representation of them has been proposed using a matrix approach. In this paper, we show how to construct Ring LFSRs and Ring FCSRs with low diffusion delay (close to the expected value n$\\sqrt {n}$) when considering other hardware cryptographic criteria."
